Citation.sAbstract: The (p, n, T) properties and apparent molar volumes (V) of LiBr in ethanol at T= (273.15 to 398.15) K and pressures up to p = 100 MPa are reported. An empirical correlation for the density of (LiBr + C2H5OH) with pressure, temperature, and molality has been derived. The experiments were carried out at molalities m = (0.23351, 0.59717, 0.94988, 1.46165, 2.27186, 2.83298, and 3.36783) mol*kg-1 using lithium bromide
Citation.sTitle: The (p, n, T) Properties and Apparent Molar Volumes V of LiBr + C2H5OH
